# Build Instructions — {{tool_name}} MCP Wrapper

> This wrapper was specified by AgentBloc Phase 3. The build session
> (Claude Code, Codex, Gemini, Cursor, OpenClaw) executes these steps
> to produce a runnable MCP server.

## Prerequisites

- `mcp-builder` skill installed (Claude Code) OR equivalent generator
  in your AI coding tool
- Bun ≥ 1.1 OR Node ≥ 20
- An API key / OAuth token for {{tool_name}} — the user provides this;
  never commit it to git

## Steps

### 1. Invoke mcp-builder

From a Claude Code session in the spec folder root:

```
/mcp-build
```

Pass:
- Tool ID: `{{tool_id}}`
- Source: `./integrations/needs-mcp-wrapper/{{tool_id}}/openapi.yaml`
- Endpoint subset: see `ENDPOINTS.md` (Included section)
- Output: `.mcp/generated/{{tool_id}}/`

The skill produces `index.ts` + `package.json` + `README.md` under
`.mcp/generated/{{tool_id}}/`.

### 2. Set environment variables

The wrapper reads these from `.env`:

| Variable | Purpose | How to obtain |
|---|---|---|
| `{{ENV_VAR_API_KEY}}` | Primary credential | {{how_to_obtain_api_key}} |
| `{{ENV_VAR_API_BASE}}` | API base URL override | Default: `{{default_api_base}}` |
{{additional_env_vars}}

Add the names to `.env.example` (no values) so future build sessions
know what to populate.

### 3. Smoke test the server

```bash
bun run .mcp/generated/{{tool_id}}/index.ts
```

Send a `tools/list` request via the MCP test harness. Expected: server
declares tools matching the Included subset in `ENDPOINTS.md`.

### 4. Register with Claude Code (or your AI coding tool)

Add to `.mcp.json`:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "{{tool_id}}": {
      "command": "bun",
      "args": ["run", ".mcp/generated/{{tool_id}}/index.ts"],
      "env": {
        "{{ENV_VAR_API_KEY}}": "${env:{{ENV_VAR_API_KEY}}}"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

Restart Claude Code so the MCP picks up.

### 5. Verify from your agent's wake.md

Reference the MCP tools by their generated names in
`agents/{{used_by_agent}}/tools.md`. Tool names follow the convention
`mcp__{{tool_id}}__<endpoint_op>`.

### 6. Add the integration to `INVENTORY.md` evidence

Once the smoke test passes, edit `integrations/INVENTORY.md` to record
the build outcome: install path, generated tools count, smoke-test
date.

## Failure modes

| Mode | Likely cause | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| `mcp-builder` rejects spec | OpenAPI invalid | `swagger-cli validate openapi.yaml`; fix and re-run |
| Auth failure (401) | Token scope insufficient | Verify scope per `ENDPOINTS.md` Authentication section; regenerate token |
| Rate limit (429) | Vendor cap hit | Honor `Retry-After`; document rate limit in `governance/audit-trail.md` |
| Wrapper missing endpoint | Subset too narrow | Amend `ENDPOINTS.md` Included; re-run `/mcp-build` |
| Wrapper exposes too much | Subset too broad | Trim `ENDPOINTS.md` Included; re-run; tighten agent's `tools.md` |

